Nikon Ambassador / Photographer / Director 
“The secret life of animals is out there - 
we are just too busy to see it.” 
Based in Finland 
@kpunkka_

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Konsta Punkka on September 08, 2021. May be an image of rabbit and nature.

node.text:
~ I’m very happy to announce that I’m an official Nikon Europe Ambassador now!✨

I have been using Nikon cameras since I started my career 12 years ago. My first own camera was Nikon d5100 that I used to capture my friends skating and my schoolmate’s music gigs. After a while I found my love to wildlife photography due to spending days and days photographing squirrels in my home town Helsinki. 
Cameras are vital part of my job to create touching wildlife portraits in the nature. No matter if I photograph arctic foxes in -30 degrees winter storm in Swedish Lapland or otters in side ways rain in Isle of Mull. I know I can trust the camera to give me the results I want. 

Here’s a collection of photos of wildlife from past few years. 
Which photo is your favorite? 😊 

@nikoneurope #nikonambassador 

📸 of me by @hannes_becker

node.text: ~ A few weeks old fox cub listening carefully my camera’s shutter sound and trying to figure out where the weird “clicky” sound is coming from. It’s been pretty slow in the wildlife photography field for the past weeks, but I’m looking forward to start capturing these wildlife and nature moments soon again as the temperatures start dropping and we are heading towards August. In the meantime I wish you all great summer days ahead and I catch up with you soonest with some unreleased photos from this summer! 😊 Which photo is your favorite? (1,2&3)?

node.text: ~ Spent some time climbing up the mountains of @swedishlapland last week. Here you can see @oskarvisaksson getting up on one of the mountain ridges in Kaskasavagge area. With the midnight sun shining trough out the night it’s an amazing feeling to stand on top of the mountain and see how the sun never goes under the horizon. Such an amazing week in the wild side of Kebnekaise region. More to come… ☀️

node.text: ~ I took this shot of a curious little fox cub a few days ago. Instead of using my longer lens to capture tight portraits I used my Nikon 70-200mm lens to get that beautiful sunrise glow on the trees in the top of the hill. After a slow and steady approach I managed to sneak just a few meters away. The fox cub didn’t seem to care too much and just kept on eating a rabbit leg for breakfast. Finland 2021

node.text: ~ The midnight sun season has officially started now here in the Nordics and I have been spending the past few weeks photographing the night hours and sleeping during the day time. Lots of different wildlife projects going on at the moment, but they are still unfinished to share anything. So in the meantime here’s a few landscape photos that I captured during my past few week’s exploration here in the Southern Finland. Which one you like the most? (1,2 or 3) 🌿
